gers   silitch joined prudential in  as chief credit officer and head of investment risk management overseeing prudential’s general account and other proprietary investment risks globally as well as maintaining and approving delegations of authority and investment policy statements   prior to joining prudential silitch held the position of chief risk officer of the alternative investment services broker dealer services and pershing businesses within bank of new york mellon he also served on the pershing executive committee   silitch joined bank of new york mellon in  as a credit trainee throughout his career at the bank he held senior positions in client management investor relations risk management loan restructuring credit portfolio management and basel compliance   he received a bachelor’s degree in economics from colby college   tags executive biographies related assets other articles in executive officers lucien alziari lata n reddy stephen pelletier timothy p harris john r strangfeld  back subject matter experts prudential business leaders can speak to you about   annuities corporate social responsibility commercial mortgages diversityinclusion fixed income group insurance global economymarkets health and wellness human resources individual life insurance investmentsmutual funds multicultural marketing real estate retirement talent technology worklife programs   related links our company investor relations corporate social responsibility our worldwide locations prudential  the environment  research  perspectives retirement income certainty solutions media center loginregister news archive featured stories my briefcase subscribe to rss press kitsfact sheets subject matter experts